London Abram Vivian
my last to you was en the p & 1 surtt, sence recd yd of 3 & 7d. the first
bainging invoyce & patt. of the bale no. 61, which is well, butt I do almost themble
to see no invoyce of any bayes, for oneles I have a 10o p come & frst I shall
be att a dead losp, & peat drireputation of my ware touse, & as I understand
Pindon is al most full, because suith sad lest above 20 bales be binde dum
last voijdge, ne de is att hull againe, yett I doubt Pindar shall come att
least a moith before him, I should be gladd to have bayes & kertyes aboard
Pindar, though thee was butt one bale of cloaches of each sort in dm
nay nather then faile if no bayes could com by Pindar, I would have one
bale sent to bronerdam or doit provided the dipatel could be accordingly, so pray
use yd utmost, to promote our Intrest. no as for mony, I amas tensibl
as you can be, that I lett you wnte for ist, yett I can not do, what I could
of my freindes bad not been sopmich frustrated of ther way on Brussel
as you know 173 „A.M. a N.C, & Indeed that hath Tindred mee much to
comply il you to yd owne desine, & seeng wee are not borne for our owne
selfs alsogleter, so must ave pat, butt Ihope te goever to demonstrate
my utmost to assist you, m. Towaters bill shall finde due denour & be
plaeed to my acctt., I go this week for Brussels when I hoye to remsorce
the cash by that I shall be ablee to send you a good suply
Londen Henry Maynaid
mij last soyeu was on the 18 suns to which referre you sence recd. yd of 78
by which I observe what you discoursed with silis naesh, lett un dave du paise
provided de makes them, as formerly I am att a loss, that I lave not 5 ge
al ready againe, te lett them not barrij lengr: sseven warner is well arrived
as soone as I see the sramett, shall advise you the needfull, the goods from
aboaud Babar ae come to sandes, I finde the bayes urappers at 43:6 jure
itt must be yd. cusoome to give that price, for I finde in the bale fromshie
north MN.15, 2 bayes att 143.6, in the balen. 21 3 bayes A.S. att 43.6, when
as in the bale n. 22 theeis one & the vee same A.S. att 36.6, which pray
examine for the vee best of them all principally from the norts are worth not or
farthing more then 36 a 37 p, have given you credit for my ½ share in the bales
30 & 31. Inclosed in the accctt of sale of last month, which please to
peruse, & finding waight note accordingly. I am not as yett in a contrsou to
asswitt, which ooo week, to yo gead I exspect shall be, because I go for Brussel
this week, to yd god., as for the northren trade, when you go to the nores shall
send you patt. for one bale of cloathes so see what yd. presence hen can effert
hetrember mee to m. Sabbarton, & sell dum that I gott bicense to press dis debtor
dere, & voye to effeet is orders
